Examples of valid and invalid programs

Valid
(functype sum (int int int))
(func sum (a b) (plus a b))
(sum 5 4)


(functype getMinElement ((int) int))	; we must provide a list defined as (int). So this list consists of integers

(functype getSecondElement ((a b c) b)) ; here we provide a tuple with some types a, b and c. The result is the value of type b.
Invalid
(setq x 5)
(functype increment (int nothing))
(func increment (a) (cond true (setq a (plus a 1)) 555)) ; can’t return a value
(increment a)

(functype getSecondElement (int) int) ; accept list of integers and returns int
(func getSecondElement (lst) (cond false (head (tail lst)) break)) ; can’t use break because a function must return int value
